<p>Installing Xterm is very simple, just use your distributionâ€™s package manager, examples:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge xterm <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo , ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>xterm <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Linux Mint , ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> xterm <span class="c"># Arch Linux, Manjaro , ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>yum <span class="nb">install </span>xterm <span class="c"># Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora , ...</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="bonus">Bonus</h1>
<h2 id="st">st</h2>
<p><img src="/assets/img/terminal/st.png" alt="st" /></p>

<p>And as a bonus you can also try SimpleTerminal or simply st. I currently use it on FreeBSD, as it is already available for the Window Manager dwm, it is very cool and easy to configure it and it is even lighter than rxvt.</p>

